# T1059.001 - Command and Scripting Interpreter: PowerShell

**MITRE ATT&CK Technique:** [T1059.001](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1059/001/)

**Tactic:** Execution

**Objective:** Execute malicious or test PowerShell scripts/commands on Windows 10 to simulate real-world attacker use of PowerShell for payload execution and living-off-the-land.

## Attack Attempts Summary

### 1. Attempt from Kali Linux (Remote Execution)
**Tools tried:**
- Impacket (`wmiexec.py`, `psexec.py`, `smbexec.py`)
- Custom PowerShell payload delivery via Impacket
- Simple host script for payload staging

**Issues Encountered:**
- Payload execution failed or returned errors
- Commands did not run reliably on the target
- Some attempts were blocked or produced no visible action on Windows 10

**Troubleshooting Done:**
- Tried different Impacket modules and command formats
- Used encoded commands and `-ExecutionPolicy Bypass`
- Created and transferred custom `.ps1` payload (example: open Edge to google.com then close browser)
- Tested basic remote connectivity

**Result:** Failed after multiple attempts. Impacket-based remote PowerShell execution was unreliable in this lab environment.

### 2. Successful Method: Atomic Red Team (Local Execution)

**Command Used:**
```powershell
# Run all tests for T1059.001
Invoke-AtomicTest T1059.001

# Or run specific tests
Invoke-AtomicTest T1059.001 -TestNumbers 1   # Classic PowerShell execution examples
Invoke-AtomicTest T1059.001 -TestNumbers 10  # Fileless / Registry-based execution
